    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2975" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑκών, ἑκοῦσα</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝεκ</span>.): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">willingly, intentionally, of
            one's own will;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑκὼν ἀέκοντί γε θῡμῷ</span>, i. e. not by
          compulsion, and yet reluctantly, <i><span class="en">Il.
            4.43</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἑκὼν δ᾽ οὐκ ἄν τις ἕλοιτο</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δῶρα θεῶν</span>), i. e. they cannot be got
          otherwise than from the gift of the gods, <i><span class="en">Il.
            3.66</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
